r>
<br>
Prelude: Lukaria's Ascenscion<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lukaria knelt for her evening prayers in the chapel of light Tunare.  Tonight she prayed for safety and a quick return for her love, Hamuro, who on this very day began a perilous quest.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp As she prayed, a figure appeared in front of her, her robes pure white and gave off a radiance of its own.  Her face was smooth and soft and beauty radiated from her.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Lukaria, my child,&quot; Tunare spoke to her, smiling, but there was something in her voice that caught Lukaria's attention.  Worry, and possibly fear.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Tunare, Mother, what is wrong, why is it that you come here tonight?&quot;  Lukaria said reaching out her hand as if to comfort Tunare.  Tunare took Lukaria's hand in her own with a caressing touch.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Come with me Lukaria, there is much that you yet do not know, and not much time to tell you.  There is a great battle coming, and i do not mean the war that is coming here on Norrath, yet they are one and the same.&quot;  Lukaria looked at Tunare bewildered, her eys fell upon Tunare with confusion.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Where are we going?&quot; she asked.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;To where the gods walk, to where the gods wage war, to the realm of the gods.&quot; Tunare answered, the smile fading from her face, and she became very serious, &quot;Will you join us?  Will you help us wage war against the gods of evil?&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I will.&quot;  Lukaria answered.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Then come with me, your training begins now.&quot;  Tunare spoke, and pulled Lukaria into her arms and together they vanished from the world of mortals, from Norrath forever.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp CHAPTER 1: Darkness Falls<br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Rorouni sat down, more fell than sat, he was exhausted from his battle with the Sarnak's at the Lake of Ill Omen.  He then heard a sound from behind him, he turned to look and saw a black mailed fist strieking for his head, he had no time to move out of the way.  The blow from the fist knocked him unconcious.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp When he woke up he looked around, he found himself in some type of prison cell and he heard voices coming form outside, one, an older persons voice that almost sounded familiar. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Is the spike ready for him?&quot;  The older voice said.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Yes Sir, the spike is ready.&quot;  Replied another voice.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Place him on it.&quot;  The older mans voice said.  Now Rorouni could see outside his cell and caught glimpses of who was talking outside.  The older one appeared to be wearing armor as black as night.  Then the cell door opened and rorouni was removed from the cell, and taken to a place where he was strapped into a lowering mechanism and was floted above the spike, he was then lowered to the tip of the spike.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Why are you doing this?&quot;  Rorouni screamed as he was being lowered, only laughter responded his cries.  Once at the tip of the spike the ropes that held him up were released, and Rorouni plummeted onto the spike, his own weight driving the spike deeper into his stomach.  His body stopped sliding down the spike about half way down, his screams echoed through the chamber.  A hand gripped his chin and forced his head up, and Rorouni stared into the old man's face, disbelief in his eyes.  &quot;Why?&quot;  he spoke, barely able to summon the strength to say that one word.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You are my proof of loyalty to Bertoxxulous, enjoy the rest of your pitiful life.&quot;  The older man dressed in the black armor spoke, then laughed malicously.  His laughter echoed through the champer and into the corridors of Bertoxxulous's Fortress.  Bertoxxulous himself, sitting in his personal chambers smiled.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You have done well for yourself, and have almost proved to me that you are truely sincere about joining me and my cause.  Don't you think Lady T'Vyl?&quot;  Bertoxxulous spoke to the man wearing the black armor, glancing behind him as Lanys T'Vyl entered the room.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Indeed my Lord, he has, but i told you that when he first came to us.&quot; Lanys responded, she walked up to the man in the black armor.  The man was very short in stature, with a long beard detailing his face, a Dwarf.  Lanys put her arms around the dwarf and kissed him on the lips.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You did indeed Lanys, but i have one more test for you.  This test if you pass will prove to me that you have truely forsaken your past and all those who belong to it.&quot;  Bertoxxulous spoke, ignoring Lanys's activities with the dwarf.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I will do as you command my Lord.&quot;  The dwarf spoke.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You will capture, and bring to me alive one whom you had for so long considered a close friend of yours.  Bring to me the Half-Elf Ranger known as Lillia.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Yes, my Lord.&quot;  The dwarf turned and left Bertoxxulous's chambers and smiled, the smile of an evil mind at work setting a trap.  As his plan's came together in his mind as he walked out of the Fortress and entered the lands of Norrath.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Back in his chamber Bertoxxulous watched the dark figure of the dwarf fade into the darkness, then turned to Lanys T'Vyl, &quot;This Hamuro of yours interests me, a Paladin, turned Dark Paladin, this has never happened on Norrath before.  I sence the tides shifting my way, as they did on the planet Draxxul, i had an army of dark Paladins there.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I have to admitt myself that his turn is hard to believe, but his gift to me was, quite extraordinary.  If i may ask my Lord, why did you send him on this as a test.&quot;  Lanys said.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I need to know if he will be capable of what i would like him to do later on.  If he handles this in such a way, everything will fall into our hands just the way we planned it.&quot;  Bertoxxulous responded to her.<br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Chapter 2: The Darkness Grows<br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lillia entered the front door to the Guild Hall and saw Esperanza almost immediately.  &quot;Any word on or from Hamuro?&quot;  Esperanza asked Lillia.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;No, i'm afraid not, i couldn't find a trace of him.  Not even his daughter knows where he has gone.&quot;  Lillia sadly responded to Esperanza.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;It isn't like him to be gone this long without any word.  I am worried that something horrible has happened to him.&quot;  Esperanza said, then walked out of the Hall.  Lillia continued to head back to her room.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lillia entered her room and went to lay down on the bed, she had been out looking for any kind of sign of hamuro to no avail, many members of the guild had begun to start to worry about him just as Esperanza was worried about him.  A silver glint coming from a desk in her room then caught her eye.  She walked over to see what it was and saw that it was a note sealed with some type of shiny silver material.  She opened the note and read it.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Dear Lillia,<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp I know you have not heard from me in some time now, i have found something that i &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp would like you to see, come to the statue on the river near Firiona Vie, come alone, &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp don't tell anyone.  I need your help with a surprise for the guild, so i beg you not to &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp tell anyone.  After you read this note please set it in a fire proof area and the silver &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp material found on the seal will consume this note in flames.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Your Dear Friend,<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lillia through the letter into the fire-place and the letter immediately burst into flames.  That very day Lillia set out for Firiona Vie.  Two days later she stood beneath the statue on the river in Firiona Vie, alone, and she waited for Hamuro to appear.  No sooner did she sit down than she heard a voice behind her, &quot;Hello old friend.&quot;  Hamuro said with a smile on his face.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;HAMURO!!!&quot;  Lillia leaped up and hugged the old dwarf almost strangling him in her arms.  &quot;It is so good to see you again.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;And you Lillia, i have missed you greatly.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;So what is it that you need my help with?&quot;  Lillia asked.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Come, i will show you.&quot; Hamuro answered, he turned away and smiled to himself.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;That is a new look for you Hamuro.&quot;  Lillia commented as they walked up-stream.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I Happened along it as i traveled, it is rather good armor, and it fits me well.  Ah, here we are.&quot;  As they rounded the bend in the river and went behind a large rock they came to their destination.  There on the ground lay the body of a man, who appeared to be dead.  Lillia knelt down to the body to get a closer look at who it might be and to see if he was still alive.  She never got that far, as she began to bend over she felt a sharp pain to the back of her neck and she collapsed to the ground, she looked back around to see her assailant and only had time to see a black gauntleted fist coming to her face.  Her jaw made a sickening sound as it snapped and broke from the blow to her face, and she fell to the ground unconscious.  The last thing she remembered thinking was, &quot;Why, Hamuro, why?&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp END OF CHAPTER 2<br>
