<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lillia awoke to find herself shackled to a wall, she was in some kind of prison cell, it was dark inside the cell, and she could tell there was not much room in this cell, barely enough to stand in and she did so.  Lillia pulled herself up to her full height and found the the tip of her head touched the ceiling.  The room was lit by only one source of light, a small barred window in what looked from what light came through to be a door.  She slowly moved forward toward the door, then the pain hit her.  She tried to cry out in the pain but just using her jaw to open her mouth sent pain coursing through her body.  She then realized that her jaw was broben in 4 places, even though she could not move her jaw, she did let out moans of pain.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Ah, the half-breed is awake.&quot;  Spoke a voice that was so familiar to her.  &quot;Heal her jaw, i want to be able to hear her screams.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp With those words a man entered her cell and placed his hands on her head and a rush of rejuvinating energy coursed through her and her jaw became whole once again.  When the cleric had finished he left the tiny cell and closed the door behind him.  Lillia pulled herself up to the door of the cell and took her first look out of the cell.  Almost as soon as she looked out she turned and hurried back to a corner of the room and wretched.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The door opened again and a dwarf dressed in jet black armor stepped in.  Hamuro reached down and the chains that help Lillia to the wall, in one hand, in the other he put a key to the wall where the chains were fastened.  The chains came undone from the wall and he help Lillia by the wrists where the chains were shackled to her. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;help me Hamuro,&quot; She said weakly.  Hamuro responded by pulling her by the chains out of the cell.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp There just outside her cell was a large iron spike, blood stained the metal on the top half of the spike.  From the point of the spike it widened as it went down.  Lillia averted her eyes from the gruesome sight near the base of the spike, but Hamuro grabbed her by the chin and forced her to look.  &quot;This is the price of opposing Lord Bertoxxulous and Lady T'Vyl, and the price of standing in my way.&quot;  At the base of the spike was what looked to be a Wood Elf male, he was laying on his stomoch impaled by the spike, the spike making a hole in his back almost large enough to cut him in two.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp What made this sight even worse for Lillia was that she knew who this unfortunate Wood Elf was, Rorouni, member of the Champions of Marr, a guild whose the hope of all of Norrath stood.  Hamuro leaned down to take Rorouni by the chin, bringing Lillia down with him.  As he lifted the chin a moan escaped Rorouni's lips.  &quot;Still alive are we?&quot;  Hamuro stated coldly, and Rorouni spit in his face.  Hamuro let go of Lillia's chin and she fell to the floor and there she wretched again.  &quot;In your position Rorouni, the slightest weight upon your back will kill you.&quot;  With that Hamuro placed his pinky on the back of Rorouni between his shoulder.  rorouni tried to scream but only gurgled up blood, and then even that ceased as the top half of his body slid off the spike, completely severed from the lower half of his body.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro turned to face Lillia and as she looked up at him, he smiled, a cruel wicked smile.  &quot;Shall i have you go through the same fate?&quot;  Hamuro took off his glove and touched the tip of the spike with his finger, and then held it out in front of Lillia, &quot;Sharp, shall it pierce your soft, smooth skin?&quot;  Hamuro got up and pulled her up with him.  &quot;No, unfortunately Bertoxxulous needs you alive.  There is no escape for you,&quot;  Hamuro then led her to a man that had to be the one in charge of this dungeon and spoke to him in harsh tones, &quot;Strip her, flay her skin with the whips and beat her until she passes out, then heal her wounds just enough so that they stop bleeding and let her regain consciousness in her cell, then start over again.  Keep doing this untill i tell you to stop.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lillia looked into Hamuro's eyes with a horrifying look in her own, she tried to see any compassion in his eyes, any sign of the Hamuro who she used to know, the Hamuro she had called a friend not two days ago.  She found nothing there in his eyes, just cold, cruel, hatred and evil burned in his eyes.  &quot;Why Hamuro, why?&quot; she said to him as he began to walk away.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro half turned his head to her and said, &quot;A great game of chess is about to begin, all the pieces must be put in place before it can begin.&quot;  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lillia screamed as they began to rip the clothes off her body, leaving her naked.  she screamed again and again as the whip cracked over her body, and between her cries of pain she heard laughter from the man whom she had called friend.  Deep, twisted, and evil laughter belowed out of Hamuro as he turned his back and began to walk out of the room.  His laughter echoed through the chamber, it echoed through the corridors.<br>
<br>
End of Chapter 3<br>
