<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro knelt in the Great Hall of Bertoxxulous's Fortress, he knelt in front of Bertoxxulous himself, with Lady Lanys T'Vyl standing not too far behind Lord Bertoxxulous.  &quot;Rise Hamuro,&quot;  Bertoxxulous's coice boomed through the Hall, &quot;You have done well for yourself and proven yourself to me that you are worthy of joining my elite forces.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Wait, my Lord.&quot;  A man also dressed in black armor shouted as he entered the Great Hall,  he wlaked up and kneeled before Lord Bertoxxulous then rose again and spoke.  &quot;This Dwarf Paladin cannot be trusted.  So he captured two of his old friends, this does not prove that his heart is truely evil, surely you can sence it my Lord.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I sence nothing but evil from the heart of this dwarf.&quot;  Bertoxxulous replied.  &quot;General Tyros, he has earned my trust, that should be enough for you as well.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Without warning Hamuro stood and through his fist into the Generals stomach, the General gasped in surprise as Hamuro's hand penetrated his armor and into his body.  &quot;Let this be a testiment of the evil that lies in my own heart.&quot;  Hamuro said and then reached his arm up into the chest cavaty of the General, up intil his fist clenched around the Generals heart, &quot;As well as a testiment of your failure to Lord Bertoxxulous.&quot;  Hamuro's hand clenched tightly around the heart of the General and he squeezed together as tightly as he could until everyone in the room heard the sound of his heart bursting.  General Tyros crumpled to the floor convulsing as Hamuro's fist came out of the hole in the General's stomach, still holding the crushed heart.  Hamuro threw the remains of the heart to the floor next to the crumpled general's body.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lord Bertoxxulous smiled, &quot;You are now my Black Knight, come with me, i will lay out your task for you now.&quot;  As he turned around to leave the Great Hall, Lanys T'Vyl walked up to Hamuro, put her arms around him and kissed him sweetly and fully.  Then, arm in arm Hamuro and Lanys followed Lord Bertoxxulous into his ante-chamber.  &quot;Hamuro, General Gorndax Dragondorf, he is the single person on Norrath that can stand in my way to complete victory.  His military prowess is well known and well respected, i even grudgingly admit by myself.  I need him out of the way.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Then i will go and kill him.....&quot; Hamuro started to say but Bertoxxulous interrupted him.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;No, i want him alive, i want you to capture him, and bring him back here, use that half-breed as bait.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro smiled, &quot;I have a better idea sir, and will get rid of another obstacle to you as well.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I'm listening.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;She is what holds that fragile alliance together to begin with, remover her from the picture, who i can then better use to trap Gorndax and pull him here without much trouble.&quot;  Hamuro started.  As he continued on with his plan, Bertoxxulous and Lanys both smiled, as they new that with this they were sure to win.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;So then, i will need a human female, that knows how to play musical instruments, one that can be molded and shaped to look exactly like her, with one excepting, instead of that of a pure heart of goodness, she will have a dark heart of evil.&quot;  Hamuro finished.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;All will be ready for you when you return.&quot;  Bertoxxulous.<br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * * * * * <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lillia lifted her head from the floor of the cell, and then the pain returned to her.  For the last two days her flesh had been ripped apart from head to two by the whips, only to be healed up again and again so that they could start all over again.  She heard a sound at the door and she pretended to be still unconscious, then she heard that voice again. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Don't worry my dear, a dear friend of yours will be joining you soon, and when she is here, all hope for Norrath will end.&quot;  Hamuro laughed deeply and vilely as he turned and left her there in the cell, and there she wept.<br>
<br>
<br>
