<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Esperanza traveled through the Commonlands on her way to Kithicor Forest.  She traveled to Highhold Keep for a meeting of the War Council, but she traveled with a heavy heart and a mind burdened with three missing Champions of Marr.  The first one was a long time friend, Hamuro, it has been five weeks since his disappearance, how could he be so cruel as to not even send any or leave any word.  The second missing member was Rorouni, he was last seen at the Sarnak Fort near the Lake of Ill Omen, no one has seen or heard from him for about a week now.  The third missing member is one that also weighs heavily on her, three days ago she left the Guild Hall without a word to anyone, she has not been seen since.  She feels that what is happening to Lillia now is what happened to Hamuro.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp With all these thoughts, she also had the responsibility of keeping the fragile alliance of guild and races from all across Norrath together.  And with all this running through her mind she did not even notice that she had come to the edge of the forest of Kithicor and she stopped in her tracks and looked around.  &quot;Dammit Esperanza you are going to get yourself killed if you don't start paying more attention.&quot; She scolded herself.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Yes you will, old friend.&quot; came a voice from the edge of the woods.  Esperanza looked at where the voice came from, wonder on her face, and she began moving at a quick pace to where the voice came from.  Just inside the forest was a small alcove, where sat a dwarf dressed in jet black armor.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;HAMURO!!!!&quot;  Esperanza said in astonishment and then ran to him and hugged him.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Esper, i have news about Lillia.&quot;  He spoke after she released him from her arms.  &quot;She was supposed to meet me three days ago, i was attacked once i got close to our meeting point and i got there just in time to see agents of Bertoxxulous carry her off.  I managed to follow them to where they took her.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Where did they take her hamuro?&quot;  Esperanza asked.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Inside His Fortress.  I believe they plan to kill her very soon now too.  Will you come with me and help me get her out, i couldn't do it by myself, i need your help, your abilities can get us in and out without a trace.  I know how to get back there, i just can't get to Lillia.&quot;  hamuro spoke those last with tears streaking down his face.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Lets go and get more from the guild to help....&quot; Esperanza began, but Hamuro interrupted her.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;No, we don't have the time, by the time we get others and head back to Bertoxxulous's Fortress Lillia may already be dead.  Time is not on our side and it is running out, we must go now, or never.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Lead the way then, Hamuro.&quot;  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro led Esperanza farther into the forest, they came up to a large tree made of some kind of black wood, Ebony, a kind of wood found rarely in any of the forests of Norrath.  Hamuro went up to the trunk of the tree and then proceeded to walk through it.  Esperanza looked at it in confusion and then followed Hamuro quickly.  When they stepped out on the other side they found themselves in a darkly lit tunnel that continued straight ahead.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;This is a tunnel that leads underneath the Fortress, this will take us to the dungeon that they were keeping Lillia in, follow me.&quot;  Hamuro spoke in a whisper.  He led her through the corridor which made only two turns and then ended in a dead end, but Hamuro pressed on a plate on the wall and the wall opened up into a small chamber.  &quot;This is the first room that we must go through to enter the dungeon, once through here we are in the dungeon.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Esperanza used her abilities to make them both invisible and they continued on through the room and they entered the dungeon.  To their surprise there were no guards, no others in the dungeon save for the prisoners, which at this time there was only one, Lillia, who they could hear moaning in pain from one of the cells, they quickly found her and with a little work Esperanza had the door open.  Tears filled her eyes when she looked upon the mass that lay huddled on the floor and she went immediately to Lillia side.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Lillia, is that really you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Esperanza!, how did you get here?&quot;  Lillia asked looking into Esperanza's eyes.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Hamuro brought me here, he...&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;NO, get out, it is a trap.&quot; Lillia said to her, just then the door to the cell slammed shut and the door relocked.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Esperanza stood and ran to the door and saw Hamuro standing there with the keys in his hand, smiling.  &quot;Hamuro, what are you doing, get us out of here.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro laughed, &quot;Esperanza, that was all too easy.  You are too predictable, you didn't even think about what i told you, just took it to be truth just because it came from someone you used to know.&quot; <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro then shouted, &quot;Jylez, strip her, we will need all of her items and armor in tact.  Tell Syremon that his model is here.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Why Hamuro, why are you doing this?&quot;  Esperanza shouted at him.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro turned to face her, &quot;The great game of chess is about to begin, more pieces need to be placed in preparation.&quot;  He then turned his back on her and walked out of the dungeon.  Esperanza sand to the floor next to Lillia, tears streaming down her cheeks, that wasn't the Hamuro that she had called a friend.  The door to the cell was opened again and three men came in and began striping her of all her belongings, her weapons, her instruments, and her armor were all removed, leaving her completely naked, just as naked as Lillia was laying next to her.  Then after the three men had left another man came in and picked up Lillia, shortly later the screams began again and Esperanza huddled in the corner of the cell, naked, with tears falling from her face.  She jumped with every sound of the whip cracking against flesh and then the sound of of Lillia screaming in pain.<br>
<br>
<br>
END OF CHAPTER 5<br>
