<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Well, Lukaria, we apologize for throughing you into things like this, i wish we had much more time to train you.&quot;  Tunare spoke to Lukaria apologetically, &quot;but i think now that you can see the desparation that we face here.  Our forces are on their heels, trying to hold, but things don't look good, Bertoxxulous and Lanys T'Vyl have gained a distinct advantage and their power continues to grow.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I will do what i can to help, I do see your plight here.  You have shown me some of the ropes of this place of where I will be fighting and what it is we are fighting to protect.  You have also shown me some of the powers i am now capable of as well, being a goddess is new to me, but i will do my best with my abilities.&quot;  Lukaria reassured Tunare, but Tunare just started to cry.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Things are even worse than you know, we have been betrayed on Norrath, by one that we had held in high respect for his dealings with Lanys T'Vyl and Innoruuk, and with his own daughter.&quot;  Tunare spoke through her tears, &quot;Hamuro has now become a Dark Paladin.  It is a rare occurance for something of this nature to happen, it has never before happened on Norrath, but dangerous.  A Dark Paladin is more powerful than anything else on Norrath, it is believed that Shadow Knights are the anti-Paladins, but they only scratch the surface of the power of a Dark Paladin.  On the planet of Draxxul, two hundred Paladins turned anti-paladin and with their combined power decimated the forces of good on that planet within hours.  Bertoxxulous won that planet in a complete route of our forces there, that was the beginning of the balance shifting to his favor.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I don't believe that Hamuro has forsaken the Light and become evil, it is not his way.&quot;  Lukaria spoke. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Then look and see for yourself, let your own eyes view his own actions.&quot;  Tunare returned.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lukaria opened up what looked to be a window out of the thin air, she was looking into a dungeon, the dungeon of Bertoxxulous's Fortress.  Hamuro stood there wearing midnight black armor, a change for him, he was looking into a cell at a woman whom she recognized.  &quot;Esperanza.&quot;  Lukaria gasped, and then listened as Hamuro began to speak.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;So, what are you going to do with me now that you have me here, Hamuro?&quot;  Esperanza spoke.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;My dear Esperanza, you should be thanking me for having you here, at least here you will not be used and lied to, back out there that is all they do to you, i didn't dare say anything then.  Here i will use you, but i am going to tell you how i am going to use you.  You see, you are my bait for capturing General Gorndax.&quot;  Hamuro spoke coldly, another change in him that Lukaria noticed.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;So you intend to trade me for Gorndax.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro smiled, &quot;In some areas you are very smart.&quot;  An Esperanza looked daggers at Hamuro.  Hamuro returned the look, &quot;Jylez, i don't think i like the way that she is looking at me, bring her out here.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Jylez opened the cell door and two men went in and dragged Esperanza out of the cell and shackled her to a table.  &quot;Her eyes offend me, which one should i pluck out?&quot; Jylez and the others laughed.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lukaria looked on in horror as Hamuro plunged his fingers into Esperanza's right eye, she screamed as Hamuro dug out her eye with his own hand, the guards held her down.  The screams continued and then Hamuro brought his hand up holding what was left of Esperanza's right eye.  Lukaria sank to the ground choking on her tears.  Esperanza's screams of pain still filled the air, and Tunare closed the window and the screams stopped, but not in her head.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;And what does Brell Serilis have to say about the betrayal of one of his own champions.&quot;  Lukaria choked out angrily.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Brell has been secluded for some time now, almost from about the time this all began with Hamuro.  No one has been able to speak with him since.&quot;  Tunare responded.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Then by all the gods we shall go have a little chat with Brell Serilis.&quot;  Lukaria screamed.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You wished a word with me?&quot;  A man's voice came from the entrance of the chamber, Brell Serilis walked forward, calmly.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;What do you have to say for yourself Brell, your champion has turned against you.&quot;  Lukaria spat.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Easy child, you may be one of us but you do not yet fully understand our ways.  That is why I am here, to make you understand what is going on, and why it is doing so.  Now sit and listen, your true lessons of godhood begin now.&quot;  Brell spoke. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;There is a reason for everything that is happenning now, i tell you these things now because you must take my place in watching over things for me, i will need all my powers to do what i have to do next.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lukaria sat and listened, she bowed her head as understanding filled her.  A single tear fell from her eye.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
END OF CHAPTER 6<br>
