<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Esperanza lay asleep in the cell she shared with Lillia, Lillia was again unconscious from the beatings and whippings she had recieved not an hour ago.  Lillia's screams still echoed in Esperanza's head, Lillia's pain was added to the throbbing of her missing eye.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Esperanza.&quot;  A woman's angelic voice pierced the haze of her pain, and the dream began.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Esperanza looked up at the woman who had spoken her name, Lukaria stepped out from the shadows and into the light.  &quot;Esperanza, i know the pain you go through, unfortunately i cannot give you all the answers, i don't have the time.  All i can tell you is this, Hamuro is fighting for good, no matter what it may look like, he is still on our our side.  When the time comes he will need your help, trust him, i beg this of you, the fate of more than just Norrath rides on his shoulders.  Now i must go, my time here has ended, trust him esperanza, good-bye.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Esperanza opened her eye, a tear streaming down her cheek, her missing eye no longer hurt, and for the first time in months Esperanza had hope, a hope she shared with Lillia when she woke.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * * * * *<br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Betrayed,&quot;  Gorndax spat and threw the letter on the table in front of Thayana, who picked it up and read it for himself.  &quot;And what is worse it is by one of our own.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I don't understand why Hamuro would turn to Bertoxxulous and join his forces.  Then to capture first Rorouni, then Lillia and then Esperanza, this makes no sence to me.  What will you do General?&quot;  Thayana asked.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Call a meeting of the Champions, and call the war council together, i will make known then what i will do.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Thayana left the room and began to summon the war council and the Champions of Marr together.  Eight hours later General Gorndax addressed them all in the Great Hall of the Champions.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;As you all know, Esperanza failed to make it to the last meeting of the War Council.  Esperanza has been captured by an agent of Bertoxxulous.  That agent was also a member of our very own guild.  Hamuro holds Esperanza hostage, he has offered me an axchange, me for Esperanza.  Hamuro also holds Lillia captive, if i do not offer myself for exchange, he will kill Lillia and Esperanza.  And so i will go, i will offer myself in exchange for Esperanza.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The room errupted into chaos.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Why would Hamuro do such a thing?&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Who will lead us?&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Who will lead the armies?&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Gorndax shouted, &quot;Quiet, please, i will have quiet.&quot;  The room immediately became quiet.  &quot;Anyone can lead the armies against the forces of Bertoxxulous.  But Esperanza is the heart of this alliance, without her everything we have fought for so long and hard will crumble to ashes.  So tomorrow i will meet with Hamuro at the edge of the Kithicor Forest.  Be there with me, to show that we stand as one against the forces of evil.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Gorndax stepped down and left the room.  For long moments the room remained silent, then everyone slowly began to file out of the chamber.  Until only five remained in the room.  Kharne, Hakko, Adrena, Dinsk, and Mortulin all sat facing each other in silence.  Kharne was the first to break the silence.  &quot;It would appear that truely dark times have fallen upon us and evil is standing at our back door.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;What are we going to do about this?&quot;  Hakko asked.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I say we follow Hamuro and Gorndax back to wherever it is that Hamuro will take him,&quot;  Adrena said.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;We can then break Lillia and Gorndax out from wherever hamuro is holding them.&quot;  Mortulin added.&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Lillia,&quot; Kharne thought to himself, &quot;I will get you out of there, no matter what it costs me&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;So, we are agreed, we will wait in hiding when Hamuro meets with Grondax and the rest of us, and after the exchange we follow them.&quot;  Dinsk confirmed the plan with them all.  Then they each in turn nodded to each other and left the room.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * * * * * <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Morning rose in the dark forest of Kithicor, the rays of sunlight just beginning to penetrate the foliage of the forest as the sun rose over the hills of the Western Commonlands.  The sunlight glinted off of Hamuro's black armor, and then off of the deep blue armor of Esperanza as they both waited along with five other soldiers from Bertoxxulous's Fortress at the edge of the forest.  Across from them stood the ranks of General Gorndax's forces, forty Champions of Marr stood behind their fearless leader.  Gorndax began to walk forward and Hamuro made a motion behind him, two guards brought out a sack, and walked to the forces of the Champions, &quot;If you attempt to follow us, this is all that will remain of Lillia when you get to her.&quot;  Hamuro shouted and the two guards unrolled the bag and Rorouni came out of it and slammed to the ground.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro then turned to Esperanza as Gorndax reached the halfway point, &quot;Go to your people.&quot;  Esperanza then began to walk toward the Champions, as she passed Gorndax she gave him a grave look.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;It will be alright Esper,&quot; Gorndax said to her.  They then continued on their ways.  Once Gorndax reached Hamuro he was disarmed then bound and gagged and then knocked unconscious.<br>
They then proceeded into the forest.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp At the same time Esperanza reached the Champions and Thayana stepped out to her, he began to cast one of his spells, after he had finished he looked at Esperanza, &quot;Wait, you are not Esperanza.&quot;  At that Esperanza unsheathed one of her blades and slashed Thayana across the chest, he fell to the ground, his life's blood flowing from his gaping wound.  Namcidem ran up to Thayana and as he crouched over him to pray for the powers of healing from his god Esperanza plunged her second blade into his back and Namcidem collapsed to the ground still conscious.  Esperanza turned with both blades in her hand as two more Champions came forward, Feyanna began to cast a spell but before she could finish Esperanza flung her dagger at Feyanna, the dagger plunged into Feyanna's throat and she gagged on her own blood and fell to the ground, dead.  Esperanza caught movement out of the corner of her eye and saw Emrystone trying to get behind her, she lunged at him, her attack much more powerful than his defense and Esperanza's blade sank into his heart.  She heard someone casting a spell behind her but when she turned around she found that she couldn't move, She had been stunned by Narvil.  Esperanza felt something heavy hit her from behind and then she collapsed.  Namcidem stood over her fallen form clutching his chest where her blade had gone through, because of his powers the bleeding had stopped and most of the damage from the wound had been repaired.  Thayana lay unconscious but no longer breathing, the essence of his life staining the ground, Feyanna lay dead Esperanza's dagger still plunged through her throat, and Emrystone lay dead as well.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Everyone else stood there in a daze, they still couldn't believe what had just happened.  They bound Esperanza and took her back to the Guild Hall, where they put her into a prison cell till they could figure out what the hell had just happened.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * * * * *<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hakko led the way through the forest following Hamuro and his men, Kharne followed close behind with Adrena, Mortulin and Dinsk.  Suddenly Hamuro stopped, he turned around and seemed to look straight at Kharne.  Hamuro seemed to sigh, then spoke out loud, &quot;Kharne, why do you bottle up inside you your true self, why do you pretend to be good?  Let go, let your true nature again take its roots in you, be what it is in your nature to be.&quot;  Hamuro then turned and continued to walk on.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Ok, that was strange, how did he see ......... &quot;  Hakko began to say and then cut off suddenly as he began to spit blood.  He looked down to see the tip of a spear sticking through his chest.  Suddenly the spear was no longer there and her gurgled and spat up more blood as he fell to the ground, dead.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Adrena, Dinsk and Mortulin stood there in shock as they watched Kharne stab Hakko through the back, and as their companion fell, Kharne turned on them as well.  First he began to attack Adrena, his spear slicing into her arm,  Mortulin and Dinsk closed in on him and he was soon overpowered and brought down.  They bound him and made sure he could not reach any of his weapons. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;What the hell just happened?&quot;  Adrena almost shouted.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Hamuro must have done something to Kharne, some kind of spell.&quot;  Mortulin replied, &quot;Whatever it was, we now lost Hamuro's trail and any hope of rescueing Lillia and Gorndax.  We better head back, you two take care of Kharne, i will carry hakko back.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * * * * *<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Back at the Guild Hall the bodies of Feyanna, Emrystone, and Thayanna were being prepared for burial as Mortulin walked in carrying Hakko, &quot;What happened?&quot;  Rocx asked as she looked upon the body of Hakko and shook her head, tears welling up in her eyes, not for the first time this night.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I should ask the same here.&quot;  Mortulin responded, &quot;Adrena, Kharne, Dinsk, Hakko and I followed Hamuro to try to rescue Lillia and Gorndax.  Hamuro saw us somehow and must have cast some sort of spell on Kharne, Kharne pierced Hakko through the back and then attacked us.  Adrena and Dinsk are taking him down to the prison for holding until we can determine what happened to him and why.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Rocx began to visibly cry as she related what happened with Esperanza's return.  Mortulin laid Hakko's body with the others and then staggered out of the chapel.  That evening a service was held for the four champions who had died this day, many tears were shed that evening as darkness descended upon the land.  Rocx, who preformed the ceremony could barely make it through the ceremony herself.  Grief ripped through the hearts of all the Champions there, the grief of the loss of four members of their rank, three of whom once sat in the chair of an officer.  The worst grief of all, was the grief of betrayal, betrayal by Hamuro, betrayal by Esperanza, and betrayal by Kharne.<br>
<br>
<br>
END OF CHAPTER 7  <br>
