<br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Welcome to my fortress, General Gorndax Dragondorf.&quot;  Bertoxxulous said smiling standing from his throne in the Great Hall.  Gorndax stood in chains not ten feet from where Bertoxxulous stood smiling down at him.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;So what will you do with me now? Kill me?&quot;  Gorndax spat in defiance.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Oh, eventually you will be killed, but not before my purpose for you has come to an end.&quot;  Bertox replied to him calmly and then turned to Hamuro.  &quot;You have done well, My Black Knight, take this Dwarf to join with his companions, then return to me in my chambers, i have plans i wish to discuss with you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Yes, My Lord.&quot;  Hamuro spoke simply and quietly, then bowed and turned to lead Gorndax down to the dungeon.  Once to the Dungeon Hamuro took the keys from the prison master and took Gorndax to the same cell that held Gorndax's companions.  Hamuro then removed the chains from Gorndax, had his Armor taken and a robe given to him, then Hamuro opened the door to the cell and Gorndax looked in and saw two forms lying in the darkness.  Hamuro pushed Gorndax into the cell, closed and loked the door behind him.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Gorndax looked down and recognized one of the forms as Lillia, he knelt down next to her and found that she was awake, &quot;Lillia,&quot; Gorndax whispered, &quot;Are you alright?  No, i can tell that you are not, but at least you are alive.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Gorndax?  Hamuro got you too?&quot;  She said weakly.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;In exchange for Esperanza yes.&quot;&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp   Hamuro laughed as he said that and Lillia began to cry.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Then you were tricked just as I was.  Esperanza is here.&quot;  Lillia said and pointed over to the other form lying on the floor, &quot;But i warn you, she has been harmed far mor than I have.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Gorndax turned around and looked at the other body, he slowly began to turn her over and she turned the rest of the way without his help.  Gorndax gasped and began to cry, &quot;Erperanza!  Your eye?  What happened to you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;My eye offended him,&quot; she said looking out the small cell window at Hamuro, &quot;so he plucked it out.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Without standing or turning Gorndax spoke to Hamuro, &quot;I swear on all that is good and holy, you will never again in this life set foot on the soil of Norrath Hamuro.&quot;  Hamuro laughed.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Make threats when it is I who is behind those bars.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Gorndax put his arm around Esperanza and helped her into a sitting position.  &quot;It is alright Gorn,&quot; She said, &quot;I feel now like i can see better with one good eye, than i could with two.  Everything that has happened has been done for a reason, though it may not be apparant at this time, the reason is still out there.&quot;  Gorndax looked at Esperanza with a confused look on his face.  Esperanza put her head on his shoulder and whispered, &quot;you will understand when the time comes.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Well Hamuro, it appears that you have tortured these two to no end, is this my fate as well?  Physical torture?  I can deal with that.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Yes, i know you can.  That is why your torture will be a psycological one.&quot;  With that the cell door was opened and men came in and picked up both Esperanza and Lillia and took them out of the cell.  Moments later they both began to scream in pain and Gorndax ran up to the cell door to see what was happening.  &quot;You will not be tortured as they are, this is your torture, the fact that you have all your strength and yet you can do absolutely nothing while your friends are put through much pain, and all you can do is watch.&quot;  Hamuro then turned and left the chamber, the women's screams echoing after him, and he smiled. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;STOP IT, STOP IT DAMN YOU.&quot; <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * * * * * <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Come in Hamuro, have a seat.&quot;  Lanys said, leading him to a padded couch where two could sit in comfort.  Bertoxxulous sat himself into a chair across from the couch.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Hamuro, you have done me well, and now it is time to fill you in on what i will need you to do next.  Which is how i am going to win this war as well.  Already my forces march on Norrath and soon full scale war will break out.  Thanks to you and your well thought out tactics you have left our most dangerous oponent weak in its command staff.  There is also an underlying reason that i wanted all three of them here alive.  In one days time i will open a rift into the plane of Charbidos, the Plane of the Demons, and i will form a pact with the demons there and they will help me win this war in one fell swoop.  To forge this pact, I need the sacrifices of three pure hearts, the hearts of the three that you have captured for me are the purest of all.  Their blood will form the bonds i need to win the ultimate victory.  So now this is what I need you to do for me, when i open this rift i will be making the promise to these demons of the sacrifices, i need you to carry out the killing of them.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I will do as you command my Lord.  Will that be all?&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Now i sence that you and Lanys wish some time alone, go, spend your time well.&quot;  Both Hamuro and Lanys got up and left Bertoxxulous's chambers arm in arm.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * * * * * <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Kharne,&quot;  Esperanza whispered to her companion in the cell.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;What do you want?&quot;  Kharne replied harshly.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I want to escape from here, i am sure that is what you want as well.  Alone we can not succeed, but together it will be easy.  Are you with me?&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Very well, but just untill we get out of here, then we go our separate ways, got it?&quot;  Kharne replied.  Esperanza nodded.  &quot;Well, why don't i get the door then.  You can make us not seen?&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I can.&quot;&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Kharne began to search his clothes for something and then with a smile pulled out a small leather container, &quot;My spair lock-picks, never leave home without them, never know when you might be in a jam like this.&quot;  He walked up to the door and began his work, after a moment there was a click and the door swung open.  Arois looked up from his seat at the sound of the door and started to get up but then his head slammed against something hard and he sank to the floor unconcious.  Esperanza and kharne quickly grabbed there items that had been locked away in a chest near the cell, then as they were ready to head out they both heard the sound of two female voices coming down the stairs heading to the prison chamber.  They both quickly hid themselves and waited for the two to enter the room, it was Rocx and Solarii.  When they saw Arois on the floor unconcious they rushed to his sideand knelt beside him getting ready to say prayers of healing to their gods.  They never had the chance to finish them.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Esperanza charged out with two swords that she found lying on the floor at Solarii.  Solarii stood up to face Esperanza and attempted to defend herself, but she stood no chance against Esperanza and Esperanza buried both swords into her chest each puncturing a lung.  Solarii cried out in pain and fell to the ground.  Rocx turned and moved to help Solarii but was stopped short as the shaft of a spear protruded through her just above her stomach and just below her heart.  Kharne pulled the spear shaft out from Rocx's body and she slumped to the floor looking at kharne with eyes that were more hurt from his betrayal than from the wound he had given her.  Kharne and Esperanza then disappeared as Esper began to play one of her songs.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Rocx then crawled over to Solarii who while still breathing was very close to death.  As Rocx reached Solarii, Arois stirred from his state of unconsciousness, when he saw what was before him he quickly moved to help rocx and Solarii.  &quot;Remove the swords from her body.&quot;  Rocx spoke, spitting blood.  &quot;I must heal her quickly or she will die.&quot;  Arois removed the swords from Solarii's chest, and then he understood what Rocx had said.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You can't!&quot;  He exclaimed, &quot; if you heal her now in your state it will kill you.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Every Cleric knows that the power of Resurrection uses the energy of the gods to transfer a part of their own life force into the one who is being Resurrected.  One of us will die here today, both of us if i do nothing.  I have accepted my fate.&quot;  Rocx crawled close to Solarii, her own life blood pouring out of her, and she craddled Solarii in her arms and then began her prayer to Brell Serilis.  Arois pulled both of them into his arms and cried as he said good-bye to Rocx.  Rocx finished her prayer and kissed Solarii on the cheek, the last of her life force went through her kiss into Solarii's still form.  As Rocx's breathing became shallower Solarii's grew stronger.  Solarii soon began to breath the regular breath of sleep and then slowly opened her eyes.  Rocx had entered an even greater sleep, the sleep of eternity, and as Solarii realized what had happened she grasped hold of both Arois and Rocx and wept, wept for the sacrifice Rocx had made for her that she may live.  Solarii and Arois wept together.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * * * * *<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lanys left Hamuro's bed later that evening, leaving Hamuro to rest.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Hamuro.&quot;  A voice spoke.  Hamuro sat up and looked around his bed chamber, seeing no one he laid back down to sleep.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Hamuro.&quot;  Came the voice again.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Who is there?&quot;  Hamuro said sitting up again.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Hamuro, remember your oath.&quot;  Hamuro did not know how but somehow that voice seemd familiar, and he knew that the voice did not come from his room, but from the depths of his heart.<br>
<br>
<br>
END OF CHAPTER 8<br>
