&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Chapter 9: Remembrance, The Dark Path.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp As Hamuro laid in his bed, the voice again come to him, &quot;Remember your path,&quot; The voice was that of a man, a deep and gravelly voice.  Hamuro closed his eyes and the dream began.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro was at home, with his daughter Shasa, who less than a year ago had been rescued from the clutches of the Dark Elves who were using her in a plot to give new life to their god Innoruuk, The process had changed her from a High Elf to a Dark Elf, a state in which she has lived ever since.  She now serves as the new High Priestess of Tunare, with Lukaria's ascencion.  <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp A soft knock came to the door of the house and hamuro went to answer the door.  When he opened the door a sence of awe enveloped him, as a Dwarf dressed in bright shining armor entered the house.  Hamuro closed the door behind him and then knelt before the Dwarf that all Dwarves knew, Brell Serilis.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Please, Hamuro, rise, i come here on urgant business.&quot;  Hamuro rose and offered Brell Serilis a place to sit, and then sat and waited for the god to speak. &quot;I have come here to ask something of you, something that is going to be very difficult for you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Ask it my lord and it will be done.&quot;  Hamuro replied, &quot; My life is...&quot; Brell stopped him with a motion of his hand.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Before you answer this i want you to know everything that is at stake, everything that what i ask will involve.  This is the hardest thing i have ever had to ask.&quot;  Brell paused and looked down as if he was summoning the courage to speak his next words.  &quot;I want to ask you to forsake your vows to me, become evil, so that you can infiltrate and get close to Bertoxxulous and his partner Lanys T'Vyl.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro could do nothing but stare at his lord.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I need you to stop them from completing their plans, for if they succeed all good on Norrath, and many other worlds will cease to exist, and evil will reign over the entire universe.  I cannot allow this to happen.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro looked up to his Lord and spoke, &quot;If this is what you wish me to do, then i will do so.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Brell shook his head, &quot;You still do not understand all the consequences of what i am asking.  First to be able to even get close enough to Bertoxxulous you must abandon everything good about yourself, your love for your friends, for Shasa, the love you have for your Guild.  And even that wont be enough, you must have a heart of evil within you.&quot;  Hamuro looked down as what Brell Serilis had just told him began to sink in.  &quot;Take my hand, i wish to show you something.&quot;  Hamuro reached out and took Brell's hand, and in his mind Hamuro saw world after world and then Brell's voice came to him, on all these worlds goodness struggles against evil in a perfect balance.&quot;  More worlds began to be pictured to Hamuro, &quot;These worlds have just recently fallen to the might of the evil of the combined forces of Bertoxxulous and Lanys T'Vyl, Good still exists on these worlds in small pockets of resistance, but they still exist.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Another world pictured itself in Hamuro's mind, &quot;This world is a world that has a wonderful treasure upon it, whoever controls this world be it good, be it evil, whoever is in control has the power to completely destroy all sources of it's opposing force, should Evil gain control of this world all traces of goodness throughout the universe will be completely wiped out.  If good controls it then all evil can be destroyed.  It has been in my charge and many other gods of good that this world cannot be allowed to be controlled by either side.  There must always be a balance between good and evil.  Norrath is the key to this world, whoever controls Norrath will gain access to the Treasure Planet.  Bertoxxulous has conquered many worlds in search of the key to this world, and now he has found it, and he plans to uleash a war upon this world.  But to ensure that he will gain victory he plans to open a rift into a Demon Plane and summon the power of the demons to sweep across Norrath, and through the Heavens where the gods themselves do battle.  With these forces at his command there will be no way to stop him.  This is what is at stake, if you do accept this you will be sacrificing everything you hold dear to you.  You may even have to fight against many of your friends from your guild.&quot;  The images in Hamuro's mind vanished and he was again in his house. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro lifted his head, tears in his eyes, &quot;I understand all that you are asking me, I will accept this mission.  Everyone has a destiny, perhaps this is mine.  Let me talk to my daughter for a moment.&quot;  Brell nodded.  Hamuro went into the other room to talk to Shasa.  Moments later she came running out, stopped to look at Brell Serilis, tears streaming down her face, then ran out of the house.  &quot;I am ready.  But tell me, how do i become evil, i cannot on my own betray what is in my very nature.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;There is an Artifact on another world known as the Heart of Darkness, once inserted into your own heart it will begin to take over, transforming your heart into pure Evil.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp One month later Hamuro returned from his quest to find this Heart of Darkness.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;From everything you have told me about this Heart, how will i be able to fight it so that when the time comes i can return to my goodness and be able to stop Bertoxxulous and Lanys T'Vyl.&quot;  Hamuro asked Brell Serilis as the prepared to insert the evil Artifact into him.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I will be with you always, Hamuro, when the time comes you will know, but you must fight with everything you have to come back to who you are now.  Knowing this, and knowing that you will most likey have to betray your friends in the guild, are you still willing to go through with this, there is still time for you to reconsider.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;As i said a month ago, everyone has a destiny, i know now that this is mine.  I am ready.&quot;  Brell Serilis nodded and began to insert the Artifact into Hamuro, along with a small of himself.  He knew that bringing Hamuro back from this evil, Hamuro would need a fragment of goodness to hold onto, he just hoped that it was enough.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Suddenly a black tendril shot out from Hamuro and struck Brell Serilis, he screamed and fell to the floor.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * * * * *<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro shot up from his bed as he woke from the dream, he shook himself fiercely, and found that he had to wipe away a tear from his eyes.  He stood and got dressed into his Armor and then grapped his weapon, he headed to where the three Champions where being prepared for the sacrifice he was about to make to summon the Demons.  Hamuro reached the room where he was to kill them and found them arranged in a triangle laying upon stone slabs, chains binding their arms and legs to the stone.  Lillia was unconscious, Gorndax and Esperanza both watched as Hamuro entered the room and went to stand next to Gorndax and prepared his blade for the final strike to complete the ritual.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp A guard came up to Hamuro and stated, &quot;They are ready.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro raised his sword above Gorndax.  &quot;Hamuro,&quot; Came a woman's voice to his mind, and then a face appeared in front of him in his mind, it was Lukaria.  &quot;Hamuro, come back to us, remember your love for all of us, your love for me.&quot;  Hamuro closed his eyes as if to shut the picture out of his mind, then the image of his daughter shasa appeared and she spoke to him, &quot;Remember your love for me, come back to me father.&quot;  More faces went through Hamuro's mind, Rocx, Lillia, Ariell, Esperanza, Clarina, Kharne, Hakko, all of his friends, then one face looked back at him, Shasa's, then another, Lukaria, &quot;I love you Hamuro, come back to me.&quot;  Lukaria spoke, her voice carrying deep into Hamuro.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro screamed as he brought his blade down onto Gorndax, there was a loud sound of metal hitting stone, and then his blade stopped.<br>
<br>
<br>
