<br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Eoman stood in the war room in front of Narvil, who had been elevated to the command of the Armies of Norrath, Eoman continued speaking his report.  &quot;All of our armies are in place in Qeynos, Freeport, and on Feydwar.  Enemy armies have also begun moving.&quot;  Narvil sighed hearing this news.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;So it begins.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Ariell is also waiting outside for you, i believe you wanted to speak with her?&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Yes I did, You had better get back to your post, and send Ariell in when you go.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Yes Narvil, may everything go well with you, and i will see you at the end of all this.&quot;  Eoman replied and then left the room.  After Eoman left Narvil got up from his desk and went over to the table that displayed a map of Norrath.  At that time Ariell entered the room.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You wanted to speak with me Narvil?&quot;  She asked.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Come, look at this.&quot;  Narvil said and pointed to the map.  Ariell walked over and looked at the section of the map that Narvil had indicated, it was the continent of Feydwar.  &quot;The Armies of Bertoxxulous are massing in ther area known as Crushbone, Orcs, Goblins,  Dark Elves, and all manner of Undead from all over the continent.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;But we have our forces in place to stop them&quot;  Ariell replied.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Yes, but no one to command them.  With Gorndax and Esperanza gone and many others amoung our ranks have fallen due to Hamuro's treachery and betrayal.  That is why i have asked to speak to you.  I would like to put you in charge of the Armies of Feydwar.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;ME? I have no ability or qualities to lead an army.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You do.  You care about a great many things, and people will follow you because of that.  I have faith in you, and i need you, please.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I will do my best.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Thank you Ariell, or i should now say General Ariell.  Choose three people to take with you as your lieutenants.  Hold them off from taking the continent.  They will most likey go after Felwithe first, then to Kaladim, as it is the Elves that hold off the access to the Dwarven homeland.  Now, go quickly, the enemy is almost ready to move from the reports that i have recieved.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I am on my way now then, Be safe, my friend.&quot;  Ariell gave Narvil a hug and then left the room.  Ariell then went to get her three Lieutenants, Gallinar, Lenexa, and Krace.  As they prepared themselves to leave, Clarina came to Ariell's room.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Ariell, i would like to go with you, it's my homeland as well, i want to be there to defend it.  My family and friends are there as well.  I know it will be dangerous, but no more dangerous to me than to you.&quot;  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp From behind Clarina came another voice.  &quot;We will keep her out of trouble as well.&quot;  Clarina turned around and saw Takar and Mindler walk up to her.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Ariell spoke, &quot;All right you three, we leave within the hour, be ready.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * * * * *<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Be healed Lukaria&quot; A woman's voice spoke above Lukaria's body.  Lukaria felt a warmth rush into her, she opened her eyes and saw a dwarven woman looking down at her with a smile.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Rocx, isn't it?&quot;  Lukaria spoke.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Rocx smiled and nodded in reply, &quot;I saw what you did with Hamuro, now at least i understand what is going on a little more.&quot;  Lukaria, with Rocx's help got to her feet.  &quot;You have to be more carefull, you are still new to all your powers.  We don't need our General here dying cause she doesn't know the limits of her own powers.  We need you at the front, Brell Serilis is doing ok now, and the war is beginning out there.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Everything now rests on Hamuro, and the ability for his friends with him now to forgive what he has done, he is the hope of Norrath and for all us gods.  He must defeat Bertoxxulous now.  But all we can do now is hope. Let's go Rocx, i will need you at my side for this battle to come.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * * * * *<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Ariell and her companions arrived in the early morning hours in Felwithe where she took over the leadership of the armies there.  She was also met with a wonderful surprise, an army of Dwarves had came to help with the defences of the forest, for they knew that if the Feydarks fell then nothing would stop the destruction of Kaladim.  That evening Gallinar burst into Ariell's study, &quot;I think you should come take a look.&quot;  Ariell followed Gallinar at a dead run, untill she reached the top of the wall and looked out over the forrest.  There where Kelethin stood, rose a large plume of smoke. <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;It can't be,&quot; Ariell gasped.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;It is, Kelethin is burning.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
