&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp CHAPTER 11: TO FIGHT EVIL<br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Gorndax felt the rush of air from Hamuro's sword and he waited for the blow that would kill him, but the blow never came, instead he heard the clang of metal on metal and then metal on stone and suddenly Gorndax could again move his arm.  Shortly after that came the same sound and his other arm was freed and then his legs, he was completely free.  As he struggled to reorient himself he heard the same sounds coming from the other two stone alters where Lillia and Esperanza were chained down.  Finally his sight came back to him and he saw Hamuro standing near him, Gorndax moved quickly and before Hamuro knew it he had his hands aournd Hamuro's neck.  &quot;Kill me and kill any hope that Norrath has left.&quot;  Hamuro choked out at Gorndax.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Esperanza recovered and looked over weakly at the two struggling dwarfs, &quot;Gorndax, listen to him, at least give him the chance to explain his actions.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp With her words Gorndax released Hamuro and said, &quot;You have untill we can get our armor and weapons back on to explain yourself, and i may still kill you.&quot;  Hamuro nodded and then moved over to Lillia and laid his hands on her.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;She is almost dead, Brell, give me the strength to heal her wounds, give her your strength as it will be greatly needed in the hour to come.&quot; As Hamuro spoke his hand began to glow a soft white glow and anergy and power and life force flowed into Lillia's broken form covering her in a soft white light.  When the light faded she was whole again, without a mark on her form from the lashings and beatings she had taken while held prisoner.  Hamuro then went over to Esperanza and again prayed to Brell for his healing touch and she too was healed leaving no marks of her imprisonment here, except one, the one thing that could not be healed, her missing eye.  &quot;Come,&quot; he finally said, &quot;I will take you to your things, and as we walk and you dress i will explain everything.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro led them to their clothing, weapons and armor, and while they dressed he explained from the beginning all that had taken place and why he had done what he had done.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Why could you not tell us, we are your friends?&quot;  Lillia asked when he had finished.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Because had he told us, the Bertoxxulious would have been able to find out much easier.&quot;  Gorndax responded.  &quot;But how do we know that you have truely overcome this evil artifact that you carry with you now?&quot;  Hamuro could only look at him in responce.  &quot;At the first sign of any betrayal then, you will die Hamuro.&quot;  Hamuro just nodded.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Wether you believe what i have just told you or not, i intend to face Lord Bertoxxulious, alone if i have to.  He cannot be allowed to proceed with what he plans.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You will not have to fight alone Hamuro, I will stand by your side.&quot;  Esperanza said, standing as she finished getting her armor on, Lillia stood next to her.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;I too, will fight with you Hamuro.&quot;  Lillia said clasping Hamuro's shoulder.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Madness,&quot; Gorndax spat, then moved to Hamuro and place his hand on his other shoulder, &quot;I guess i am in with you as well, let's go kill a god.&quot;  All four of them then walked out, Hamuro in the lead.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * * * * *<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;The time is almost here.&quot;  Lanys said, &quot;By now the blood of the three companions should be staining the floor, the sacrifice to the demon gods has been made.&quot;  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lanys T'Vyl and Lord Bertoxxulous stood in the center of a vast chamber.  Wide columns lined the walls of the chamber.  In the center of the chamber was an alter surrounded by a black circle, it is hear that Bertoxxulous and Lanys T'Vyl stood, performing the last rites of the ritual that would open the gateway to the realm of the demon-kind.  In front of them was the stairway the led Hamuro and his three companions into the dark chamber.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Upon seeing Hamuro Lanys moved up to him from the alter, &quot;Well done, my love.&quot;  It was then that she saw the three that accompanied him, &quot;TRAITOR!!&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Espeanza and Lillia came up to Hamuro's side, &quot;Let us take care of this one, you and Gorndax go after Bertoxxulous himself.&quot;  With that they moved in and engaged the evil woman as Hamuro and Gorndax moved on to Bertoxxulous.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You are a great deciever, Hamuro, bearer of the Dark Heart, but you are still too late, the demons have already been summoned and will be here soon, you have failed.&quot;  As Hamuro and Gorndax stepped within the dark ring encircling the altar, an earthquake struck the chamber. The floor surronding the dark circle split apart and a great chasm opened separating the dark circle from the rest of the chamber floor by four feet and the sound of shieking demons could be heard from within.  Hamuro and Gorndax charged the evil god, but Bertoxxulous was ready, with a flash Hamuro was flung across the room and slammed into the wall, Hamuro sank to the floor unconcious.  Gorndax closed in on the god, Bertoxxulous drew his sword and engaged the General in single combat.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lillia and Esperanza fought a desparate battle against the daughter of darkness Lanys T'Vyl but found themselves losing ground.  Lanys forced them ever closer to the chasm, her swords whirling about her to block and parry her attackers attacks and then landing attacks of her own wherever a defence was exposed.  As the neared the edge of the chasm Lanys delivered a crushing blow to Esperanza's head and she collapsed in a heap leaving Lillia to fight her alone.  Lillia looked to her fallen friend and her eyes narrowed in determination and renewed strength.  Both women had tried to use their spells to aid them but found that in this room their magic did not function.  And so Lillia pressed on her opponent with furiosity, Lanys was caught off-guard by this new round of attacks and was forced to retreat her position.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Gorndax fought with furosity against the dark god but was no match for him, Bertoxxulous parried every blow Gorndax threw at him, and then returned by landing devastating blow after blow.  With a mighty swing Bertoxxulous sent Gorndax's sword flying through the air and with a vicious punch sent the dwarf sprawling to the floor, his wind knocked out of him.  Bertoxxulous stood over him his sword raised to deliver the death blow, &quot;This is the price of defying me!&quot;  His sword arched down on the dwarf struggling to regain his strength, and was met with the ring of steel on steel as another sword materialized out of nowhere above Gorndax.  &quot;YOU, TRAITOR, now i will kill you with my bare hands.  Hamuro stood there in front of the dark god and smiled.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;My destiny has already been chosen, and now i will send you to meet yours.&quot;  Hamuro spoke calmly.  Their swords clashed, Bertoxxulous fumed with rage and anger and sent rage filled blow after blow at Hamuro who calmly blocked them.  But Hamuro soon began to lose ground, never finding the opportunity to strike with his own attacks.  Another blow pushed Hamuro ten paces away from the dark lord and to the edge of the chasm.  Hamuro looked up at the dark Lord and smiled raising his sword above his head, Bertoxxulous charged,  his blade pierced through Hamuro's black armor into his lung and through his body.  Hamuro grabbed hold of Bertoxxulous's wrists as the momentum of the charge carried him over the edge and into the chasm, only then did Bertoxxulous realize his mistake.  Hamuro grabbed for the edge of the chasm and caught himself from falling,  Bertoxxulous clung to the hilt of his sword as the demons rushed up from the pit, the demons grabbed hold of Bertoxxulous and wrenched his grip from the hilt of the sword stuck fast into Hamuro's chest.  The Dark Lord screamed as he plummeted into the pit.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro began to slip from the edge of the chasm, the pain from his wound overcoming him, but just as he began to fall a hand grasped his and then another, and they began to pull him up from the chasm.  As he reached the top of the chasm the scream of a woman pierced the air, Hamuro and Gorndax looked over and saw Lanys T'Vyl disengage from her battle with Lillia and run to the edge of the chasm where she leapt over sword ready to come down on the unprepared Dwarves.  Suddenly a blue armored arm reached up and grabbed hold of her leg and caused her to come to a stop over the center of the great chasm, she screamed as she began to plummet into the pit after her master Bertoxxulous.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Lillia went over to Esperanza and helped her to stand, putting her arm around her to support her.  Gorndax finished pulling Hamuro out of the chasm and then began to remove the sword from his chest, Hamuro cried out in pain as the sword came out and Gorndax began to speak, &quot;Brell, bring down your life force onto your servant who sacrificed so much to see that evil would not rule this land or any other land, give him your blessing and restore his strength.&quot;  As he spoke his hands began to glow a soft white and that glow began to spread over Hamuro's body untill he was completely engulfed in the pure white light of the power of Brell Serilis.  When the glow faded the two dwarves stood and then leapt to the other side of the chasm.  &quot;Come on, it is time for us to get out of here.&quot;  Hamuro said, holding his chest where the Bertoxxulous's blade had entered &quot;I know the way.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Hamuro led them to the passage that he had used many times under the orders of the Dark God, but as the entered the teleportation room they were spotted by the guards who came after them. &quot;How many are there?&quot;  Lillia asked.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Twenty or more.&quot;  Gorndax replied, &quot;We'll never make it out of the fore...&quot;  It was then that he noticed that Hamuro had stayed back at the door into the room with the teleporter.<br>
&quot;Hamuro, no, it's suicide.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;The porter is there, just press that button while standing on the platform, go, i will buy you time.&quot;  Hamuro said.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;We can't allow you to do this Hamuro,&quot; Lillia said stepping up to him.  &quot;you will never make it passed so many, not in your condition.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;GO, you are needed by many more.  My destiny is complete, yours has just begun Lillia, go now, i will hold them back long enough for you to make your escape.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Gorndax went up to Lillia and took her by the hand, &quot;come, let his sacrifice mean something.&quot;  With those words all three stepped onto the platform pressed the button and activated the platform, as the began to dissappear Hamuro turned and charged at the guards coming after them.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp * * * * *<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Eoman looked up from the western walls of the city of Freeport, and as he looked toward the Lavastorm mountains his heart froze and he began to shake in fear as a massive beast with wings colored in the red of blood and fire rose the dragon known as Nagafen.  Nagafen let out a great roar and began his flight toward the commonlands.<br>
<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp END OF CHAPTER 11<br>
